ository, WorkItemStatusHistoryRepository (do NOT inject RcdoWeekRollupRepository — RCDO coverage is computed from commits' rcdoNodeId fields, not from the rollup table). Method simulate(WhatIfRequest): WhatIfResponse that: (a) loads plan + commits from DB, (b) builds currentState snapshot (total points, budget, per-RCDO points, risk signals computed by re-implementing the 5 rules logic inline — do NOT call RiskDetectionService.detectAndStoreRiskSignals which persists), (c) clones commit list in-memory, applies mutations (ADD inserts synthetic, REMOVE filters out, MODIFY updates), (d) builds projectedState from mutated list, (e) computes deltas. Returns WhatIfResponse with narrative=null. Replicate OVERCOMMIT/UNDERCOMMIT/REPEATED_CARRY_FORWARD/BLOCKED_CRITICAL/SCOPE_VOLATILITY rule thresholds from RiskDetectionService (duplicate as package-private constants). Throw ResourceNotFoundException if plan not found.\n\n4. `backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/service/WhatIfServiceTest.java` — @ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class) unit test matching RiskDetectionServiceTest pattern. Mock all repositories. Test cases: (a) ADD_COMMIT pushes over budget → OVERCOMMIT in projectedState.riskSignals, (b) REMOVE_COMMIT brings under budget → resolves OVERCOMMIT, riskDelta shows resolved, (c) MODIFY_COMMIT changes rcdoNodeId → rcdoCoverageChanges shows point shift, (d) empty mutations → currentState equals projectedState, (e) plan not found → ResourceNotFoundException.",
