r via constructor, following the pattern in CommitDraftAssistService and RiskDetectionService). If AI unavailable (!result.available()), return response with narrative=null, recommendation=null. Inject both AiProviderRegistry and ObjectMapper via constructor (update the constructor created in step 1 to add these two dependencies).\n\n6. Add endpoint in `backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/controller/AiController.java` — @PostMapping(\"/api/ai/what-if\") accepting @Valid @RequestBody WhatIfRequest, calls WhatIfService.simulate(), returns ResponseEntity<WhatIfResponse>. Add WhatIfService to constructor params/fields. Follow commitDraftAssist endpoint pattern.",
